erited from BaseEntity |\n35: | `deleted_at` | `timestamp` | NULLABLE | Soft delete timestamp |\n36: \n37: **Indexes:**\n38: - `UNIQUE` on `email`\n39: - `INDEX` on `role`\n40: - `INDEX` on `status`\n41: - `INDEX` on `(role, status)` composite\n42: \n43: **Relationships:**\n44: - `hasMany` → `RefreshToken` (one user has many refresh tokens)\n45: - `hasMany` → `PasswordResetToken` (one user has many reset tokens)\n46: - `hasMany` → `Favorite` (one user has many favorites)\n47: - `hasMany` → `Inquiry` (one user submits many inquiries)\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ### RefreshToken\n52: \n53: Stores JWT refresh tokens for rotation and invalidation. Each refresh creates a new row; the old row is marked deleted when rotated. Not extending `BaseEntity` (no need for update timestamps or soft delete — expiries handle lifecycle).\n54: \n55: **Table:** `refresh_tokens`\n56: \n57: | Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n58: |-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n59: | `id` | `uuid` | PK, default: `uuid_generate_v4()` | Primary key |\n60: | `user_id` | `uuid` | FK → `users.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE CASCADE | Owning user |\n61: | `token` | `varchar(500)` | NOT NULL, UNIQUE | Encoded JWT refresh token string |\n62: | `expires_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL | Token expiration time (7 days from issue) |\n63: | `revoked_at` | `timestamp` | NULLABLE | Set when token is rotated or user logs out |\n64: | `created_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Token creation time |\n65: \n66: **Indexes:**\n67: - `UNIQUE` on `token`\n68: - `INDEX` on `user_id`\n69: - `INDEX` on `expires_at`\n70: \n71: **Relationships:**\n72: - `belongsTo` → `User` via `user_id`\n73: \n74: ---\n75: \n76: ### PasswordResetToken\n77: \n78: Stores tokens for the forgot-password / reset-password flow. Tokens expire after a configurable window (e.g., 1 hour).\n79: \n80: **Table:** `password_reset_tokens`\n81: \n82: | Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n83: |-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n84: | `id` | `uuid` | PK, default: `uuid_generate_v4()` | Primary key |\n85: | `user_id` | `uuid` | FK → `users.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE CASCADE | Owning user |\n86: | `token` | `varchar(500)` | NOT NULL, UNIQUE | Secure random reset token |\n87: | `expires_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL | Token expiry (e.g., 1 hour from creation) |\n88: | `used_at` | `timestamp` | NULLABLE | Set when password is successfully reset |\n89: | `created_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Token creation time |\n90: \n91: **Indexes:**\n92: - `UNIQUE` on `token`\n93: - `INDEX` on `user_id`\n94: \n95: **Relationships:**\n96: - `belongsTo` → `User` via `user_id`\n97: \n98: ---\n99: \n100: ### Property\n101: \n102: Represents a rental property listing. Supports soft delete (archiving). Address fields are stored as individual columns for search/indexing; API layer nests them into an `address` object.\n103: \n104: **Table:** `properties`\n105: \n106: | Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n107: |-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n108: | `id` | `uuid` | PK, default: `uuid_generate_v4()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n109: | `title` | `varchar(200)` | NOT NULL | Listing title (5–200 chars) |\n110: | `description` | `text` | NOT NULL | Full description (20–5000 chars) |\n111: | `price` | `decimal(10,2)` | NOT NULL | Monthly rent (> 0) |\n112: | `bedrooms` | `integer` | NOT NULL, CHECK (≥ 0) | Number of bedrooms |\n113: | `bathrooms` | `integer` | NOT NULL, CHECK (≥ 0) | Number of bathrooms |\n114: | `square_feet` | `integer` | NULLABLE, CHECK (> 0) | Living area in square feet |\n115: | `property_type` | `enum` (`PropertyTypeEnum`) | NOT NULL | `apartment` \\| `house` \\| `condo` \\| `townhouse` \\| `studio` |\n116: | `address_street` | `varchar(200)` | NOT NULL | Street address |\n117: | `address_city` | `varchar(100)` | NOT NULL | City |\n118: | `address_state` | `varchar(100)` | NOT NULL | State / province |\n119: | `address_zip_code` | `varchar(10)` | NOT NULL | ZIP / postal code |\n120: | `address_latitude` | `decimal(10,7)` | NULLABLE | Geocoordinate latitude (-90 to 90) |\n121: | `address_longitude` | `decimal(10,7)` | NULLABLE | Geocoordinate longitude (-180 to 180) |\n122: | `available_from` | `date` | NULLABLE | Date property becomes available |\n123: | `created_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n124: | `updated_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n125: | `deleted_at` | `timestamp` | NULLABLE | Soft delete / archive timestamp |\n126: \n127: **Indexes:**\n128: - `INDEX` on `property_type`\n129: - `INDEX` on `price`\n130: - `INDEX` on `bedrooms`\n131: - `INDEX` on `bathrooms`\n132: - `INDEX` on `address_city`\n133: - `INDEX` on `address_state`\n134: - `INDEX` on `(address_latitude, address_longitude)` — geospatial queries\n135: - `GIN INDEX` or `tsvector` on `title || ' ' || description || ' ' || address_city || ' ' || address_state` for full-text search (optional, for performance at scale)\n136: \n137: **Relationships:**\n138: - `hasMany` → `PropertyPhoto` (one property has many photos)\n139: - `belongsToMany` → `Amenity` via `property_amenities` junction\n140: - `hasMany` → `Favorite` (one property is favorited by many users)\n141: - `hasMany` → `Inquiry` (one property receives many inquiries)\n142: \n143: ---\n144: \n145: ### PropertyPhoto\n146: \n147: Stores uploaded photos for a property. Multiple photos per property with ordering and a primary photo designation.\n148: \n149: **Table:** `property_photos`\n150: \n151: | Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n152: |-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n153: | `id` | `uuid` | PK, default: `uuid_generate_v4()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n154: | `property_id` | `uuid` | FK → `properties.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE CASCADE | Owning property |\n155: | `url` | `varchar(500)` | NOT NULL | Photo URL (S3 / CDN path) |\n156: | `is_primary` | `boolean` | NOT NULL, default: `false` | Whether this is the main/thumbnail photo |\n157: | `sort_order` | `integer` | NOT NULL, default: `0` | Display order in gallery |\n158: | `created_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n159: | `updated_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n160: \n161: **Indexes:**\n162: - `INDEX` on `property_id`\n163: - `INDEX` on `(property_id, sort_order)`\n164: \n165: **Business Rule:** Only one photo per property may have `is_primary = true`. Enforced at the application layer.\n166: \n167: **Relationships:**\n168: - `belongsTo` → `Property` via `property_id`\n169: \n170: ---\n171: \n172: ### Amenity\n173: \n174: Predefined list of amenities that can be associated with properties. Managed by admins.\n175: \n176: **Table:** `amenities`\n177: \n178: | Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n179: |-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n180: | `id` | `uuid` | PK, default: `uuid_generate_v4()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n181: | `name` | `varchar(50)` | UNIQUE, NOT NULL | Amenity name (e.g., \"parking\", \"gym\") |\n182: | `icon` | `varchar(50)` | NOT NULL | Icon identifier for frontend rendering |\n183: | `created_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n184: | `updated_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n185: | `deleted_at` | `timestamp` | NULLABLE | Soft delete |\n186: \n187: **Indexes:**\n188: - `UNIQUE` on `name`\n189: \n190: **Relationships:**\n191: - `belongsToMany` → `Property` via `property_amenities` junction\n192: \n193: ---\n194: \n195: ### PropertyAmenity\n196: \n197: Junction table for the many-to-many relationship between `Property` and `Amenity`. Each row links one property to one amenity.\n198: \n199: **Table:** `property_amenities`\n200: \n201: | Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n202: |-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n203: | `property_id` | `uuid` | PK (composite), FK → `properties.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE CASCADE | Property reference |\n204: | `amenity_id` | `uuid` | PK (composite), FK → `amenities.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE CASCADE | Amenity reference |\n205: \n206: **Primary Key:** Composite `(property_id, amenity_id)`\n207: \n208: **Indexes:**\n209: - `INDEX` on `amenity_id`\n210: \n211: **Relationships:**\n212: - `belongsTo` → `Property` via `property_id`\n213: - `belongsTo` → `Amenity` via `amenity_id`\n214: \n215: ---\n216: \n217: ### Favorite\n218: \n219: Represents a renter saving a property to their favorites. Idempotent — adding a duplicate returns the existing record (API handles this). Composite unique constraint prevents duplicates.\n220: \n221: **Table:** `favorites`\n222: \n223: | Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n224: |-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n225: | `id` | `uuid` | PK, default: `uuid_generate_v4()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n226: | `user_id` | `uuid` | FK → `users.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE CASCADE | The renter who favorited |\n227: | `property_id` | `uuid` | FK → `properties.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE CASCADE | The favorited property |\n228: | `created_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n229: \n230: **Indexes:**\n231: - `UNIQUE` on `(user_id, property_id)` — prevents duplicate favorites\n232: - `INDEX` on `user_id`\n233: - `INDEX` on `property_id`\n234: \n235: **Relationships:**\n236: - `belongsTo` → `User` via `user_id`\n237: - `belongsTo` → `Property` via `property_id`\n238: \n239: ---\n240: \n241: ### Inquiry\n242: \n243: Represents a contact/inquiry submission from a renter about a specific property. Admins manage inquiry status and responses.\n244: \n245: **Table:** `inquiries`\n246: \n247: | Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n248: |-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n249: | `id` | `uuid` | PK, default: `uuid_generate_v4()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n250: | `property_id` | `uuid` | FK → `properties.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE SET NULL | Subject property |\n251: | `user_id` | `uuid` | FK → `users.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE SET NULL | Submitting renter |\n252: | `name` | `varchar(100)` | NOT NULL | Submitter's name (denormalized for display) |\n253: | `email` | `varchar(255)` | NOT NULL | Submitter's email (denormalized) |\n254: | `phone` | `varchar(20)` | NULLABLE | Submitter's phone (denormalized) |\n255: | `message` | `text` | NOT NULL | Inquiry message body (10–2000 chars) |\n256: | `status` | `enum` (`InquiryStatusEnum`) | NOT NULL, default: `'new'` | `new` \\| `read` \\| `responded` |\n257: | `response` | `text` | NULLABLE | Admin's response text |\n258: | `responded_at` | `timestamp` | NULLABLE | Set when admin responds |\n259: | `created_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n260: | `updated_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n261: \n262: **Note:** `name`, `email`, `phone` are denormalized from the `User` record at submission time. This preserves the inquiry even if the user account is later deleted (hence `ON DELETE SET NULL` on `user_id`).\n263: \n264: **Indexes:**\n265: - `INDEX` on `property_id`\n266: - `INDEX` on `user_id`\n267: - `INDEX` on `status`\n268: - `INDEX` on `(status, created_at)` — for admin dashboard filtering\n269: \n270: **Relationships:**\n271: - `belongsTo` → `Property` via `property_id`\n272: - `belongsTo` → `User` via `user_id`\n273: \n274: ---\n275: \n276: ## Enums\n277: \n278: ### RoleEnum\n279: \n280: Used in `users.role`.\n281: \n282: | Value | Description |\n283: |-------|-------------|\n284: | `renter` | Standard user who browses and saves properties, submits inquiries |\n285: | `admin` | Administrator with full system access |\n286: \n287: ---\n288: \n289: ### UserStatusEnum\n290: \n291: Used in `users.status`.\n292: \n293: | Value | Description |\n294: |-------|-------------|\n295: | `active` | Account in good standing |\n296: | `suspended` | Account suspended by admin; cannot log in |\n297: \n298: ---\n299: \n300: ### PropertyTypeEnum\n301: \n302: Used in `properties.property_type`.\n303: \n304: | Value | Description |\n305: |-------|-------------|\n306: | `apartment` | Apartment unit |\n307: | `house` | Single-family house |\n308: | `condo` | Condominium |\n309: | `townhouse` | Townhouse |\n310: | `studio` | Studio apartment |\n311: \n312: ---\n313: \n314: ### InquiryStatusEnum\n315: \n316: Used in `inquiries.status`.\n317: \n318: | Value | Description |\n319: |-------|-------------|\n320: | `new` | Unread inquiry (default on submission) |\n321: | `read` | Viewed by admin |\n322: | `responded` | Admin has sent a response |\n323: \n324: ---\n325: \n326: ## Relationships\n327: \n328: ### Entity Relationship Diagram\n329: \n330: ```\n331: users (1) ────────< (many) refresh_tokens\n332: users (1) ────────< (many) password_reset_tokens\n333: users (1) ────────< (many) favorites\n334: users (1) ────────< (many) inquiries\n335: \n336: properties (1) ───< (many) property_photos\n337: properties (1) ───< (many) favorites\n338: properties (1) ───< (many) inquiries\n339: properties (many) >────< (many) amenities  [via property_amenities]\n340: ```\n341: \n342: ### Foreign Key Summary\n343: \n344: | Child Table | FK Column | Parent Table | On Delete |\n345: |-------------|----------|--------------|-----------|\n346: | `refresh_tokens` | `user_id` | `users.id` | CASCADE |\n347: | `password_reset_tokens` | `user_id` | `users.id` | CASCADE |\n348: | `property_photos` | `property_id` | `properties.id` | CASCADE |\n349: | `property_amenities` | `property_id` | `properties.id` | CASCADE |\n350: | `property_amenities` | `amenity_id` | `amenities.id` | CASCADE |\n351: | `favorites` | `user_id` | `users.id` | CASCADE |\n352: | `favorites` | `property_id` | `properties.id` | CASCADE |\n353: | `inquiries` | `property_id` | `properties.id` | SET NULL |\n354: | `inquiries` | `user_id` | `users.id` | SET NULL |\n355: \n356: ### Relationship Details\n357: \n358: | Relationship | Type | Owner | Inverse | Junction |\n359: |-------------|------|-------|---------|----------|\n360: | User → RefreshToken | One-to-Many | — | RefreshToken.user ↔ User.refreshTokens | — |\n361: | User → PasswordResetToken | One-to-Many | — | PasswordResetToken.user ↔ User.resetTokens | — |\n362: | User → Favorite | One-to-Many | — | Favorite.user ↔ User.favorites | — |\n363: | User → Inquiry | One-to-Many | — | Inquiry.user ↔ User.inquiries | — |\n364: | Property → PropertyPhoto | One-to-Many | — | PropertyPhoto.property ↔ Property.photos | — |\n365: | Property → Favorite | One-to-Many | — | Favorite.property ↔ Property.favorites | — |\n366: | Property → Inquiry | One-to-Many | — | Inquiry.property ↔ Property.inquiries | — |\n367: | Property ↔ Amenity | Many-to-Many | Property (JoinTable) | Property.amenities ↔ Amenity.properties | `property_amenities` |\n368: \n369: ---\n370: \n371: ## Conventions\n372: \n373: ### Timestamps\n374: - All `timestamp` columns use `default: now()` for `created_at`.\n375: - `updated_at` is auto-managed by TypeORM (`@UpdateDateColumn`).\n376: - `deleted_at` is managed by TypeORM soft-delete (`@DeleteDateColumn`).\n377: \n378: ### Soft Delete\n379: - Enabled on: `users`, `properties`, `amenities`.\n380: - NOT enabled on: `refresh_tokens` (managed via `revoked_at` + `expires_at`), `password_reset_tokens` (managed via `expires_at` + `used_at`), `favorites` (hard delete on unfavorite), `inquiries` (retained indefinitely for audit), `property_photos` (hard delete on removal), `property_amenities` (junction – hard delete on unlink).\n381: \n382: ### Naming\n383: - **Tables**: `snake_case` plural (e.g., `property_photos`, `password_reset_tokens`)\n384: - **Columns**: `snake_case` (e.g., `user_id`, `property_type`, `address_city`)\n385: - **Enums**: PascalCase suffix `Enum` in TypeScript (e.g., `RoleEnum`, `PropertyTypeEnum`)\n386: \n387: ### Data Types\n388: - Monetary values: `decimal(10,2)` (supports prices up to $99,999,999.99)\n389: - Geo-coordinates: `decimal(10,7)` (sub-meter precision)\n390: - Percentages/ratios: `decimal(5,2)` if needed in future\n391: \n392: ---\n393: \n394: *Generated: 2026-05-19 | Source: PROJECT_KNOWLEDGE.md + PROJECT_API.md + database-patterns.md*\n\n(End of file - total 394 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# PROJECT_DATABASE\n\n## Schema Overview\n\nAll entities extend `BaseEntity` which provides:\n- `id` — UUID primary key\n- `createdAt` — `timestamp` (auto-managed)\n- `updatedAt` — `timestamp` (auto-managed)\n- `deletedAt` — `timestamp | null` (soft delete support)\n\nColumn naming convention: `snake_case` in the database (`@CreateDateColumn({ name: 'created_at' })`).\n\n---\n\n## Entities\n\n### User\n\nRepresents all registered users (Renters and Admins). Extends `BaseEntity` with soft delete.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude-project/nestfind/docs/PROJECT_DATABASE.md","time":{"start":1779174602307,"end":1779174602600}},"id":"prt_e3f11f01d001gbNnVcAJQCmV6z","sessionID":"ses_1c0ee2e9dffeeIp7JCrE0l02GJ","messageID":"msg_e3f11d55e001lXcnxv6If5HCVc"}}
